# IAM directory boundary (`lib/auth/`)

## Authority

- **`lib/auth/`** owns the **IAM control plane**: Better Auth configuration, session/step-up guards, **audit writers** ([`audit.server.ts`](lib/auth/audit.server.ts) + `iam_audit_event` in [`lib/db/schema.ts`](lib/db/schema.ts)), and **permission predicates** ([`permission.server.ts`](lib/auth/permission.server.ts) — org role + global admin only; no duplicate RBAC trees in `app/` or features).
- **`app/`** owns **routes and UI** only (`/sign-in`, `/account`, `/admin`, `/dashboard`, `/api/auth/*`). Do not introduce an `app/iam/*` URL tree for configuration authority.

## Import rules

- **Public server door:** import `auth` from `#lib/auth` only (resolved to [`lib/auth/index.ts`](lib/auth/index.ts)). Import guards such as `requireRecentAuthStepUp` from `#lib/auth` as well.
- **Do not** deep-import `lib/auth/config.server.ts` from `app/` or from ERP feature modules unless `AGENTS.md` explicitly allows it; prefer `#lib/auth`. **Exception (cycle avoidance):** low-level `lib` modules that must load the Better Auth instance before the barrel re-exports (e.g. [`lib/session-cache.ts`](lib/session-cache.ts)) may import `#lib/auth/config.server` only — not from `app/`.
- **Shared path helpers** (no React): e.g. [`lib/auth/callback-path.ts`](lib/auth/callback-path.ts) may be imported as `#lib/auth/callback-path` from server or client when the symbol is intentionally shared. **Proxy-safe header names** for path intent: [`lib/auth/forwarded-path-headers.shared.ts`](lib/auth/forwarded-path-headers.shared.ts) (Edge `proxy.ts` must not import `server-only` / `next/headers` helpers). **Canonical auth interruption codes** live in [`lib/auth/auth-status.shared.ts`](lib/auth/auth-status.shared.ts); bookmarkable URLs via [`lib/auth/auth-interruption-url.shared.ts`](lib/auth/auth-interruption-url.shared.ts); server redirect + intended path in [`lib/auth/interruption-redirect.server.ts`](lib/auth/interruption-redirect.server.ts) + [`lib/auth/intended-path.server.ts`](lib/auth/intended-path.server.ts). UI copy resolver [`lib/auth/auth-status-copy.ts`](lib/auth/auth-status-copy.ts).

## Proxy and validation

- **[`proxy.ts`](proxy.ts)** stays **narrow**: cookie presence, redirects, matcher only — **no** business logic, **no** DB, **no** session body validation.
- **Post-login `callbackUrl`** must be validated for **open redirects** (same-origin relative paths only). Server Components should resolve/validate before passing props to client islands.

## ERP modules

- **Do not** embed IAM workflows inside `lib/features/<module>/` beyond calling guards or `#lib/auth` APIs exported for that purpose.

## Evidence / object storage

- **R2 / archive / long-lived evidence** are **storage roadmap** concerns. Document policy in `AGENTS.md` / env as needed; **implementation follows** once IAM audit semantics are stable — they **must not block** IAM control-plane PRs.

## Audit action names

- ERP/org events use **`erp.<module>.<object>.<verb>`** and **`org.<object>.<verb>`** (see **IAM audit policy (ERP)** in `AGENTS.md`). Session hooks keep **`iam.session.*`**.

## Contract changes

- New filenames under `lib/auth/` or new IAM categories require updating **`AGENTS.md`** in the same change.
